article.description: Khallid Hart scored 27 points and hit four 3-pointers and Marist roared back in the final 2:59 to hand Dartmouth its third straight loss 75-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Marist powers past Dartmouth behind Hart's 27 points
article.linkText: Marist powers past Dartmouth behind Hart's 27 points
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Khallid Hart scored 27 points and hit four 3-pointers and Marist roared back in the final 2:59 to hand Dartmouth its third straight loss 75-69 on Saturday. Miles Wright hit a 3-pointer with 2:59 remaining to put Dartmouth up 67-65. But from there the Big Green (0-3) went cold and the Red Foxes stormed back to finish the game on a 10-2 run. Kristinn Palsson immediately answered Wright's triple with a 3 of his own to recapture the lead for Marist. However a Hart 3 with 18 seconds left gave the Red Foxes (2-4) a 73-67 lead and proved to be the dagger. Brian Parker finished with 17 points and 10 rebounds form Marist, which shot 52.9 percent from the field. Evan Boudreaux led the Big Green with 17 points and 10 boards. Wright added 16 and Guilien Smith had 15 for Dartmouth.
